<BasicLayout
  title="About Multi-Family USA | Multi-Family USA"
  description="We publish neutral US multifamily financing guidance for operators evaluating 5+ unit properties—underwriting, capital markets, and execution."
  canonical="/about"
  enPath="/about/"
  esPath="/es/about/"
  crumbs={[
    { label: "Home", href: "/" },
    { label: "About", href: "/about" },
  ]}
>
  <h1>About</h1>
  <p>
    Multi-Family USA publishes practical educational guidance for US commercial multifamily
    financing on 5+ unit properties.
  </p>

  <h2>Our focus</h2>
  <p>
    We focus on underwriting quality, debt execution strategy, and market context that helps
    operators make better financing decisions. Our core coverage includes agency, bridge, bank,
    FHA/HUD, and CMBS-oriented frameworks used in US multifamily transactions.
  </p>

  <h2>What this site is for</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Helping sponsors structure lender-ready assumptions before quote requests.</li>
    <li>Explaining trade-offs across debt products and capital-stack choices.</li>
    <li>Providing tools for scenario testing and stress-sensitive underwriting.</li>
    <li>Publishing market-oriented pages for state and city financing context.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What this site is not</h2>
  <p>
    We do not provide legal, tax, or accounting advice and we do not publish financing
    guidance for one-to-four-unit residential lending. Content is educational and should
    be paired with licensed professionals and lender-specific guidance.
  </p>

  <h2>Editorial stance</h2>
  <p>
    Our editorial goal is transparent, execution-focused analysis. We prioritize clarity on
    assumptions, downside risk, and practical next steps over promotional claims or product hype.
  </p>

  <h2>Need transaction-specific feedback?</h2>
  <p>
    If you want a practical review of a live deal, use our
    <a href="/deal-review">free deal review</a> and share your assumptions, business plan,
    and target execution path.
  </p>
</BasicLayout>
